    "what_description": "Gamochaeta serranoi is a species of flowering plant in the family Asteraceae. It is a perennial herb that grows 5-15 cm tall, with a rosette of leaves that are 5-15 cm long and 2-5 cm wide, having serrated margins and a glabrous surface. The inflorescence is a solitary capitulum, 2-4 cm in diameter, composed of 10-20 florets, with yellow corollas 5-8 mm long and 1-2 mm wide, and 3-5 mm long anthers. The plant produces achenes, 4-6 mm long, with a glabrous surface and a pappus of 10-15 bristles, 1-2 mm long. Gamochaeta serranoi is native to Argentina and Chile.",
