    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Gamochaeta serranoi are antioxidant, antimicrobial, anti-inflammatory, and antipyretic. Its antioxidant properties help protect cells from oxidative damage, potentially contributing to its anti-aging and anticancer effects. The bioactive compounds responsible for these properties include flavonoids, which are also found in high concentrations of saponins and volatile oils. Gamochaeta serranoi's antimicrobial properties inhibit the growth of various microorganisms, including bacteria and fungi, which can cause infections. Additionally, its anti-inflammatory properties may help reduce pain and inflammation, while its antipyretic properties can help lower fever, making it a potential treatment for conditions like fever, infections, and inflammatory diseases.",
