    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Gamochaeta serranoi are sesquiterpenoid lactones, including serragamone, and flavonoids, including quercetin and kaempferol. These compounds have been shown to possess anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, which contribute to the plant's potential therapeutic benefits. Serragamone has been found to exhibit cytotoxic activity against certain cancer cell lines, while quercetin has been demonstrated to have antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory effects. Kaempferol has been reported to possess anti-cancer and anti-inflammatory properties, and has been shown to inhibit the growth of cancer cells. Additionally, Gamochaeta serranoi has been found to contain sesquiterpenoids with anti-inflammatory and antioxidant activities, which may contribute to its potential therapeutic effects.",
