    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Gamochaeta serranoi are tea, infusion, tincture, salve, and decoction. These preparations are derived from its leaves, which are traditionally used in folk medicine in the Andes region. The leaves can be made into a tea by steeping them in hot water to produce a bitter-tasting liquid, rich in flavonoids and sesquiterpenes. A tincture can be made by soaking the leaves in ethanol to create a concentrated liquid extract, while an infusion is similar to tea but with a higher leaf-to-water ratio. A decoction is prepared by boiling the leaves in water to release their volatile oils, and a salve is made by infusing the leaves in a carrier oil to produce a topical remedy for skin issues.",
